Agentic AI Platform for Enterprise Workflow Automation
Problem Statement

Many enterprise workflows across internal tools and web applications remain manual, repetitive, and fragmented.

Teams rely on human-driven navigation across multiple systems for tasks like data retrieval, reporting, approvals, and operational updates.

Existing automation solutions are rigid, expensive to maintain, and lack contextual reasoning.

Organizations lack a centralized platform to create, govern, reuse, and scale AI-driven workflow agents securely.

Solution Overview

A governed Agentic AI Platform delivered via a browser extension and backend control platform that enables teams to create and deploy autonomous agents capable of executing multi-step workflows across enterprise systems.

The platform introduces an internal agent marketplace where teams can publish, discover, and reuse domain-specific agents.

Key Benefits

Automation of Complex Workflows
Execute multi-step processes across multiple applications autonomously.

Reusable Agent Marketplace
Teams can publish and reuse agents across business units.

Enterprise Governance
Access control, domain whitelisting, audit logging, and compliance monitoring.

Rapid Deployment
Browser extension delivery allows automation without deep system integration.

Productivity Gains
Reduce manual effort and accelerate operational workflows.

